Keep in mind, though, this was also true of solar power, once upon a time. =
When Jimmy Carter put solar panels on the White House roof, it really was a=
 gimmick =E2=80=94 the technology was nowhere near cheap enough to be feasi=
ble as the basis for our electrical needs. Fast forward four decades, and s=
olar has come down in cost by a factor of 400 [https://email.mg2.substack.c=
om/c/eJw1Ud3O2yAMfZpw14i_pHDBxbStrxERcFM2AgjIqrz9nK-bhHyMjbF9jrMdtlxPU3Lr5D=
